 :tx/rationale "AUDIT-EXT POLICY-UNWIRED (from AUDIT_REPORT Section 2.3 + 5.1): PolicyConfig is well-designed but ignored by the rest of the kernel. PROBLEM: PolicyConfig (policy.rs) is SOUND — well-designed with BoundaryDef, AnomalyDef, CalibrationConfig, and WeightAdjustment types. But compute_fitness() in bilateral.rs ignores PolicyConfig weights and uses hardcoded constants (bilateral.rs:80-92). The policy manifest architecture exists but the rest of the kernel doesn't use it. This makes policy.rs architecturally correct but operationally dead for fitness computation. JUSTIFICATION: This is the paradox at the heart of C8: the solution exists (policy.rs) but the rest of the code bypasses it. compute_fitness_from_policy() exists in policy.rs but Store::fitness() falls back to MaterializedViews when no policy datoms are present — and since Layers 1-4 are hardcoded rather than transacted via policy, the fallback always activates. The policy system is a chicken-and-egg problem: it needs policy datoms to work, but policy datoms aren't transacted because the hardcoded path works. SOLUTION: This is the same fix as F-C8-001 (schema to policy manifests). Once braid init transacts policy datoms, compute_fitness_from_policy() becomes the primary path, and the hardcoded MaterializedViews fallback can be deprecated. VERIFICATION: After policy manifest adoption, grep 'W_VALIDATION\\|W_COVERAGE\\|W_DRIFT' bilateral.rs returns zero results (weights come from policy). DEPENDENCIES: Requires F-C8-001. This is the downstream benefit of moving schema to policy. FINDING SOURCE: AUDIT_REPORT.md Sections 2.3, 5.1. FILES: crates/braid-kernel/src/policy.rs, bilateral.rs. SEVERITY: High. WAVE: 2. EFFORT: Included in F-C8-001."
